  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p Two distinct blues represent the sky and water.
      hr
      small PMS and hex values provided by the Minnesota State Emblems Redesign Commission.
    .visual
      .colors.primary
        .color
          .sample(class='sky-blue')
          .name Night Sky Blue
          .hex #002C5A
          .pantone PMS 648
        include includes/color-white
        .color
          .sample(class='water-blue')
          .name Water Blue
          .hex #73C6E5
          .pantone PMS 305
  .guide
    .content
      h2 Construction
      p The Minnesota flag is produced with the common proportion of 3:5. The proportion and spacing for the flag’s visual elements are rendered here.
      p The star is a regular octagram, constructed from 8 vertices arranged equally around a circle. Each vertex is connected to the vertex that is 3 turns away.
    .visual
      +construction(name, path)

  .guide.wide.timeline
    .content
      h2 Previous iterations
      ul.visual.flag-list
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-minnesota-1893-1957-obverse.jpg', alt='field of white charged with the state seal; “Minnesota” is below, flanked by red ribbon')
          h4 1893-1957 Obverse
          p Original two-sided design by Amelia Hyde Center.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img(src='/assets/images/flag-minnesota-1893-1957-reverse.jpg', alt='the same as the obverse, but with a field of blue')
          h4 1893-1957 Reverse
          p The reverse of Center’s design, later deemed too complicated for mass production.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img(src='/assets/images/flag-minnesota-1957-1983.jpg', alt='a field of dark blue charged with the seal')
          h4 1957-1983
          p The seal is updated, blue darkened, and reverse removed.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img(src='/assets/images/flag-minnesota-1983-2024.jpg', alt='a field of medium blue charged with the sealg')
          h4 1983-2024
          p The flag with medium blue and updated seal.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img(src='/assets/images/flag-minnesota-thumb.svg', alt='the current Minnesota flag')
          h4 2024-Present
          p The current flag designed by Andrew Prekker and Minnesota State Emblems Redesign Commission.

